2. COMPANY CONTEXT (25 points maximum)
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

STEP 1: IDENTIFY CURRENT COMPANY

From results[0].basic_info.current_company:
- Primary company name
- Or extract from first is_current: true experience entry

**If multiple current positions:**
- Primary company: Usually listed first
- Consider which company is most relevant
- Note if person has multiple roles (consultant, advisor, etc.)

STEP 2: ASSESS COMPANY CHARACTERISTICS

From ICP_Profile.md, review:
- "Company Size" section (ideal employee ranges)
- "Industries We Target" section
- "Geographic Markets" section

**Company Size Assessment:**

You won't have employee count in person profile data, but infer from:
- Company name recognition (well-known companies = larger)
- Multiple office locations mentioned in experience.location
- Job title sophistication (VP at startup vs VP at enterprise)
- Description complexity in experience.description

Score based on inferred fit to ICP_Profile.md ranges:

**Perfect Fit (25 points):**
- Company characteristics strongly suggest size in "sweet spot" from ICP_Profile.md
- Industry clearly matches (if determinable)
- Geography in "Primary Markets"

**Strong Fit (20 points):**
- Company likely in "acceptable range" from ICP_Profile.md
- Industry appears to match or adjacent
- Geography in secondary markets

**Moderate Fit (15 points):**
- Company possibly in acceptable range
- Industry might fit
- Serviceable geography

**Weak Fit (10 points):**
- Limited company context available
- Size/industry unclear but not disqualifying
- Geography unknown or less ideal

**Cannot Determine (8 points):**
- Insufficient company information
- Cannot assess size, industry, or location
- Note in justification

**Poor Fit (0 points):**
- Company clearly doesn't match ICP_Profile.md criteria
- Wrong industry (if determinable)
- Geography in excluded markets

STEP 3: GEOGRAPHIC ASSESSMENT

From results[0].basic_info.location.full:
- Extract country and region
- Match against ICP_Profile.md "Geographic Markets"

Consider:
- Person's location may differ from company HQ
- Remote workers may be anywhere
- Location indicates market they serve

