SPECIAL HANDLING INSTRUCTIONS
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

**When multiple current positions (multiple is_current: true):**
- List all current roles in profileSummary
- Score based on highest-ranking role
- Note multiple roles in extractedData.hasMultipleCurrentRoles: true
- Explain in justification which role was used for scoring

**When job title has emojis or special characters:**
- Remove them from normalized title
- Original: "GTME @ StackOptimise âš™ï¸" â†’ Normalized: "GTME"
- Note the cleaning in justification

**When title is acronym or unclear:**
- Check basic_info.headline for clarification
- Look at experience.description for role context
- Look at experience.skills[] for relevant skills
- Make best inference, note uncertainty

**When no description in experience entries:**
- Rely on title and company context
- Use headline for additional context
- Check skills[] if available
- Score based on what's available, note limitation

**When assessing company context without direct company data:**
- Use company name to infer (well-known brands)
- Consider if current_company matches known companies in target market
- Note inference vs direct data
- Score conservatively if very uncertain

**When person has creator status (is_creator: true):**
- Weight profile quality higher
- Review creator_hashtags[] for market relevance
- Consider as positive signal for thought leadership
- May indicate influence beyond job title

**When follower/connection counts are very high:**
- Indicates professional presence and influence
- May suggest person is influencer or thought leader
- Consider in profile quality scoring
- Could offset lower title rank in some cases

**When geographic location doesn't match typical markets:**
- Note if person is remote (common in person data)
- Remote workers may serve primary markets despite location
- Consider where their company is based
- Don't over-penalize for remote work situations

**When profile data seems sparse:**
- Note in dataQualityNote
- Score conservatively
- Explain limitations in justification
- Recommend qualifying further vs hard disqualification

